      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secrets Rotation for LLM API Keys"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM API keys are high-value credentials: a leaked OpenAI or Anthropic key grants immediate access to expensive model inference with costs billed to your account. Unlike database passwords, a compromised LLM key can generate thousands of dollars in fraudulent charges within hours. Automated rotation on a fixed schedule \u2014 and immediate rotation on suspected compromise \u2014 is non-negotiable for production GenAI services."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rotation must be zero-downtime: pods in a Kubernetes cluster cannot restart every 30 days. The correct architecture provisions a new key, validates it, swaps the secret store entry, lets the orchestration layer propagate the update, and only then revokes the old key."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "LLM API key rotation workflow with dual-key window and per-provider schedule"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vault-Backed Key Storage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Store LLM API keys in HashiCorp Vault (or AWS Secrets Manager) rather than Kubernetes Secrets. Vault provides versioning, access audit logs, and a lease system that enables automated rotation without manual kubectl commands."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Vault KV structure for LLM keys\n# Path convention: secret/genai/<env>/<provider>/api-key\n\nvault kv put secret/genai/prod/openai/api-key \\\n    value=\"sk-prod-...\" \\\n    rotated_at=\"2024-01-15T00:00:00Z\" \\\n    rotated_by=\"rotation-bot\" \\\n    version=\"v42\"\n\nvault kv put secret/genai/prod/anthropic/api-key \\\n    value=\"sk-ant-...\" \\\n    rotated_at=\"2024-01-15T00:00:00Z\" \\\n    rotated_by=\"rotation-bot\" \\\n    version=\"v18\"\n\n# Read with versioning \u2014 rollback to previous version if new key fails\nvault kv get -version=41 secret/genai/prod/openai/api-key\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ExternalSecret Operator (ESO) syncs Vault secrets into Kubernetes Secrets automatically. Pods read via env vars \u2014 they never call Vault directly. When Vault is updated, ESO propagates the change within 60 seconds."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated Rotation Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A GitHub Actions workflow runs on a schedule and on manual trigger. It provisions a new key via the provider's admin API, validates it with a lightweight smoke test, updates Vault, and revokes the old key after a grace window."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/rotate_llm_key.py\n\"\"\"\nRotates an LLM provider API key with zero-downtime dual-key window.\nUsage: python3 rotate_llm_key.py --provider openai --env prod\n\"\"\"\nimport argparse, time, logging, json, datetime\nimport hvac          # pip install hvac\nimport openai        # pip install openai\n\nVAULT_ADDR = \"https://vault.internal\"\nGRACE_SECONDS = 300   # 5-minute dual-key window\n\nlog = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ndef rotate_openai_key(vault_client: hvac.Client, env: str) -> None:\n    vault_path = f\"secret/genai/{env}/openai/api-key\"\n\n    # 1. Read current key (keep for grace window)\n    current = vault_client.secrets.kv.v2.read_secret_version(path=vault_path)\n    old_key_value = current[\"data\"][\"data\"][\"value\"]\n    old_key_id = current[\"data\"][\"data\"].get(\"key_id\", \"unknown\")\n\n    # 2. Create new key via OpenAI Admin API\n    admin_client = openai.OpenAI(api_key=old_key_value)\n    new_key = admin_client.api_keys.create(name=f\"rotation-{env}-{int(time.time())}\")\n    log.info(\"Created new OpenAI key: %s\", new_key.id)\n\n    # 3. Validate new key works\n    test_client = openai.OpenAI(api_key=new_key.secret_key)\n    test_client.models.list()  # raises on auth failure\n    log.info(\"New key validated successfully\")\n\n    # 4. Write new key to Vault (ESO picks it up within 60s)\n    vault_client.secrets.kv.v2.create_or_update_secret(\n        path=vault_path,\n        secret={\n            \"value\": new_key.secret_key,\n            \"key_id\": new_key.id,\n            \"rotated_at\": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \"Z\",\n            \"rotated_by\": \"rotation-pipeline\",\n        }\n    )\n    log.info(\"Vault updated, waiting %ds for propagation + grace window\", GRACE_SECONDS)\n    time.sleep(GRACE_SECONDS)\n\n    # 5. Revoke old key\n    admin_client2 = openai.OpenAI(api_key=new_key.secret_key)\n    admin_client2.api_keys.delete(old_key_id)\n    log.info(\"Old key %s revoked\", old_key_id)\n\n    write_audit_log(env, \"openai\", old_key_id, new_key.id)\n\ndef write_audit_log(env: str, provider: str, old_id: str, new_id: str) -> None:\n    import boto3\n    record = {\n        \"ts\": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \"Z\",\n        \"env\": env, \"provider\": provider,\n        \"old_key_id\": old_id, \"new_key_id\": new_id,\n    }\n    s3 = boto3.client(\"s3\")\n    key = f\"rotation-audit/{env}/{provider}/{record['ts']}.json\"\n    s3.put_object(Bucket=\"genai-secrets-audit\", Key=key,\n                  Body=json.dumps(record), ContentType=\"application/json\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Actions Rotation Workflow"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/rotate-llm-keys.yml\nname: Rotate LLM API Keys\n\non:\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 3 1 * *'   # 03:00 UTC on the 1st of every month\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      provider:\n        description: 'Provider to rotate (openai | anthropic | all)'\n        required: true\n        default: 'all'\n      environment:\n        description: 'Target environment'\n        required: true\n        default: 'prod'\n      reason:\n        description: 'Reason for manual rotation (required for audit)'\n        required: true\n\njobs:\n  rotate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: production\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # OIDC for Vault auth\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Authenticate to Vault via OIDC\n        uses: hashicorp/vault-action@v2\n        with:\n          url: ${{ secrets.VAULT_ADDR }}\n          method: jwt\n          role: rotation-pipeline\n\n      - name: Rotate keys\n        run: |\n          python3 scripts/rotate_llm_key.py \\\n            --provider ${{ github.event.inputs.provider || 'all' }} \\\n            --env ${{ github.event.inputs.environment || 'prod' }}\n\n      - name: Post rotation summary to Slack\n        if: always()\n        uses: slackapi/slack-github-action@v1\n        with:\n          channel-id: ${{ secrets.SLACK_OPS_CHANNEL }}\n          slack-message: |\n            *LLM Key Rotation* ${{ job.status == 'success' && ':white_check_mark:' || ':x:' }}\n            Provider: ${{ github.event.inputs.provider || 'all (scheduled)' }}\n            Env: ${{ github.event.inputs.environment || 'prod' }}\n            Reason: ${{ github.event.inputs.reason || 'scheduled rotation' }}\n        env:\n          SLACK_BOT_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.SLACK_BOT_TOKEN }}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Break-Glass Emergency Rotation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a key is suspected or confirmed to be leaked \u2014 via a secret scanning alert, a billing spike, or an external report \u2014 the rotation must be immediate. Break-glass skips the normal schedule and revokes first, then provisions a replacement."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/break_glass_rotate.py\n\"\"\"\nEmergency key rotation: revoke immediately, provision replacement, alert ops.\nUse when: key leaked, billing anomaly, scanner alert.\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, datetime, json, os\nimport hvac, openai, boto3\n\ndef break_glass(provider: str, env: str, incident_id: str) -> None:\n    vault_path = f\"secret/genai/{env}/{provider}/api-key\"\n    vault = hvac.Client(url=os.environ[\"VAULT_ADDR\"],\n                        token=os.environ[\"VAULT_TOKEN\"])\n\n    current = vault.secrets.kv.v2.read_secret_version(path=vault_path)\n    compromised_key = current[\"data\"][\"data\"][\"value\"]\n    compromised_key_id = current[\"data\"][\"data\"].get(\"key_id\", \"unknown\")\n\n    # REVOKE IMMEDIATELY \u2014 accept brief outage to stop bleeding\n    admin = openai.OpenAI(api_key=compromised_key)\n    admin.api_keys.delete(compromised_key_id)\n    print(f\"[BREAK-GLASS] Revoked compromised key {compromised_key_id}\")\n\n    # Write INVALID marker to Vault so pods fail fast (better than using a revoked key)\n    vault.secrets.kv.v2.create_or_update_secret(\n        path=vault_path,\n        secret={\"value\": \"REVOKED\", \"revoked_at\": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \"Z\",\n                \"incident\": incident_id}\n    )\n\n    # Provision replacement (operator completes out-of-band)\n    print(f\"[BREAK-GLASS] Key revoked. Create a replacement key via the provider console\")\n    print(f\"[BREAK-GLASS] Then run: python3 scripts/update_vault_key.py --provider {provider} --env {env}\")\n\n    # Alert\n    boto3.client(\"sns\").publish(\n        TopicArn=os.environ[\"OPS_SNS_TOPIC\"],\n        Message=json.dumps({\"severity\": \"CRITICAL\", \"incident\": incident_id,\n                            \"action\": \"llm_key_revoked\", \"provider\": provider, \"env\": env}),\n        Subject=f\"[BREAK-GLASS] LLM key revoked: {provider}/{env}\",\n    )\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    break_glass(sys.argv[1], sys.argv[2], sys.argv[3])\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In a break-glass scenario it is better to accept 30\u201360 seconds of outage while rotating than to leave a compromised key active. LLM providers can rack up $10k+ charges in minutes via automated abuse."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting Leaked Keys Before They Are Used"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prevention is cheaper than rotation after a breach. Configure gitleaks in pre-commit and in CI to catch accidental key commits. Configure the LLM provider's secret scanning webhook (GitHub Advanced Security, Trufflehog) to alert your ops channel immediately."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .gitleaks.toml \u2014 rules for LLM provider key patterns\n[extend]\nuseDefault = true\n\n[[rules]]\nid = \"openai-api-key\"\ndescription = \"OpenAI API Key\"\nregex = '''sk-[a-zA-Z0-9]{48}'''\ntags = [\"key\", \"openai\"]\n\n[[rules]]\nid = \"anthropic-api-key\"\ndescription = \"Anthropic API Key\"\nregex = '''sk-ant-[a-zA-Z0-9-_]{90,}'''\ntags = [\"key\", \"anthropic\"]\n\n[[rules]]\nid = \"google-ai-studio-key\"\ndescription = \"Google AI Studio Key\"\nregex = '''AIzaSy[0-9A-Za-z-_]{33}'''\ntags = [\"key\", \"google\"]\n\n[allowlist]\nregexes = [\n    '''sk-ant-api03-EXAMPLE''',   # docs / test fixtures\n    '''sk-EXAMPLE-KEY''',\n]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
